<br>
Given all the changes of late, I think Skald resist chants should either stack (I thought they already did...if not, please see if this can be changed), or be the dual resist buffs.<br>
<br>
Granted, when we have multi-skald groups, we usually have someone turn on matter resist to counter the insane albion AOE DOT with power relics (180/hit, 6 ticks is it??), but running single line resists is kind of a waste of &quot;group support&quot; ability.<br>
<br>
Seriously, we have 2 group support songs...run, fight.  Multi-skald groups are boosted only slightly.  On the other hand, our pals the paladins, have heal/damage/af/resists/end regen?  5 options?  Some folks think paladins need the compensation, but that's folklore.  Fight a paladin that has faith heal (full group insta heal..wtf), IP, slam, endurance regen, buffed AF, and you'll find that you're outclassed.  They have more HP, they have access to anytime stun, they have 2 full insta heals, better AF, better absorb, and far, far better group enhancement.<br>
<br>
I don't think dual resist chants are out of the question, and I'd love to see ANOTHER group enhancing fight song that skalds could play when they already have darkness damage adds or a skald playing dmg song.  Many of the previous suggestions were good (i.e. group haste song)<br>
